plain what\nappears as cometary activity over a period of 8 months. However, while Main\nBelt comets best explained by ice sublimation are found in the outskirts of the\nMain Belt, where water ice is believed to be able to survive buried in\nmoderately large objects for the age of the solar system deeply, the presence\nof volatiles in an object smaller than 300m in radius would be very surprising\nin the inner asteroid belt.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jan 2014 17:48:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-23"}
